about.description:
It is a Python API for recursively localizing file URIs
(e.g. gs://. s3://, http:// and local path) on any target directory URI.
about.summary: Recursive localization for various types of URIs

name: autouri
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "autouri" %}
{% set version = "0.1.3" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: db3533f04729f08e73a90fcaf27bd53b932cbcdff93b461d7cca505448ff4cd3

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - requests
    - pyopenssl
    - google-cloud-storage
    - boto3
    - awscli
    - dateparser
    - pytest
    - filelock

test:
  imports:
    - autouri

about:
  home: https://github.com/ENCODE-DCC/autouri
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Recursive localization for various types of URIs'
  description: |
    It is a Python API for recursively localizing file URIs
    (e.g. gs://. s3://, http:// and local path) on any target directory URI.
  dev_url: https://github.com/ENCODE-DCC/autouri

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - leepc12
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.16
